  "title": "Accountant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Overview</strong></p>\n<p>We are seeking a detail-oriented and reliable Accountant to join our team. The ideal candidate will be responsible for maintaining accurate financial records, managing accounts payable and receivable, preparing financial statements, ensuring compliance with relevant regulations, and liaising with external auditors and tax agents.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p>\n<p>- Record, categorize, and reconcile all financial transactions in the general ledger to ensure accuracy and completeness of financial data</p>\n<p>- Manage accounts payable and receivable, including processing invoices, ensuring timely payments to vendors, and following up on outstanding receivables</p>\n<p>- Prepare and maintain balance sheets and profit/loss statements, providing management with clear and timely reports on the company’s financial performance</p>\n<p>- Ensure compliance with internal financial policies and external regulations, maintaining up-to-date knowledge of relevant accounting standards and practices</p>\n<p>- Liaise with external auditors and tax agents, providing necessary documentation and support during audits and tax filings</p>\n<p>- Assist in the preparation of tax returns and support other financial reporting and analysis as required</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<p>- Relevant qualification in Accounting, Finance, or a related field.</p>\n<p>- Proven experience as an Accountant or in a similar role.</p>\n<p>- Strong knowledge of accounting principles, financial regulations, and reporting requirements</p>\n<p>- Proficiency with accounting software (SAP) and MS Excel.</p>\n<p>- Excellent attention to detail, organizational, and analytical skills.</p>\n<p>- Strong communication skills to effectively collaborate with internal teams and external partners.</p>",
